                      <td width="100%" height="42">
                        <p align="left"><font size="1" face="Verdana"><span id="postcolor0">(<span id="normalname0">June21bride</span></span><span id="normalname1">)<br>
                        </span><span id="postcolor"><b>I am torn about our
                        centerpieces. &nbsp;I want something inexpensive yet
                        original</b> </span><span id="normalname">...<br>
                        </span></font>
                        </p>
                        <p align="left"><font size="1" face="Verdana"><span id="postcolor1">(<span id="normalname2">Mike&amp;Sarah3103</span></span><span id="normalname3">)</span><span id="postcolor"><br>
                        We are doing simple glass hurricanes with white ball
                        candles&nbsp;with a piece of silk ivy around them.
                        &nbsp;Simple, yet classy&nbsp;</span><span id="postcolor"><br>
                        </span></font>
                        </p>
                        <p align="left"><font size="1" face="Verdana">(<span id="normalname4">MrsMills2b)</span><br>
                        My FMIL and myself are making ceramic cowboy boot vases
                        (to go with the theme) and putting a few sunflowers in
                        them.&nbsp;<br>
                        &nbsp;</font>
                        </p>
                        <p align="center"><span id="postcolor"><a href="http://www.talkaboutweddings.com/cgi-bin/ikonboard/ikonboard.cgi?s=3e1b71424f18ffff;act=ST;f=13;t=2"><font face="Verdana" size="1">Click
