              <td width="341" height="1254" valign="top" colspan="2">
                  <table border="0" cellpadding="8" cellspacing="5" width="116%" height="1264">
                    <tr>
                      <td width="100%" height="1242" valign="top">
                        <p class="MsoNormal"><font size="2" face="Verdana"><font color="#000080"><b>Focus
                        on the Altar</b></font><br>
                        <br>
                        When selecting flowers for the ceremony, spend your
                        money on flowers where they will be seen the most.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
                        When budgeting for the ceremony - focus on the
                        altar.&nbsp;</font></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal"><font size="2" face="Verdana">If
                        you're on a tight budget -- skip the pew decorations or
                        make them yourself! </font><a href="http://usabride.com/wedplan/a_pewbows.html"><font size="2" face="Verdana">Click
                        Here for Tips on Pew Bows</font></a><span style="font-family:Arial">.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>
                        <hr noshade size="1" color="#9966CC" width="92%" align="left">
                      <p class="MsoNormal" align="left"><b><font color="#000080" face="Verdana" size="2">&quot;Best
                      Thing About My Wedding&quot;</font></b></p>
                        <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><font size="2" face="Verdana">Lisa,
                        Wedding Date: Nov 13, 2000<br>
                        DEFINITELY, having our Pictures taken BEFORE the wedding
                        ceremony! There is such controversy about this issue,
                        but we had such a wonderful time. It made everyone more
                        relaxed at the ceremony, and left us with much more time
                        to socialize and dance at the reception. The day goes by
                        so fast that I was so thankful to have those extra hours in the afternoon with my
                        husband-to-be.&nbsp;</font></p>
                      <p class="MsoNormal" align="left"><font face="Verdana" size="2"><span style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Giselle,
                        Wedding Date: May 22, 2000</span><br>
                      I had a Wedding Coordinator
                        - which I totally recommend. I feel many Brides feel
                        stressed because they try to do it &quot;all&quot;
                        themselves.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Our
                        Wedding Coordinator did everything we wanted and more.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
                        </span>She was the one who ran around the day of the
                        Wedding getting my flowers, all the bridesmaids
                        headpieces done with fresh flowers and I did not have to
                        worry about anything!&nbsp;</font></p>
                              <p align="left"><b><font color="#000080" face="Verdana" size="2">&quot;What
                              I Would Do Differently About My Wedding&quot;</font></b></p>
                              <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Verdana"><span style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Sarah,
                        Wedding Date: Nov, 19 2000</span><br>
                        I would have gone with a bridal shop that's been in
                        business for at least 5 years.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
                        </span>The shop that I went with was only open a few
                        months and didn't know how to do business with people.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
                        </span>Once they got our money they become very rude.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>
                              <br>
                        </span>They didn't order my bridesmaid dresses until
                        Sept 1 (should have been ordered in June) and they arrived
                              5 days before our wedding.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
                        </span>They were upset with me because I found out the
                        ship date of my dresses.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
                        </span>They told me to take all our dresses out of the
                        shop and find someone else to do the alterations, which
                        wasn't easy.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></font></p>
                        <p align="left"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Want More
                        Bride Advice?&nbsp; Sign up for our &quot;Best Thing and
                        What I Would Do Differently&quot;
                        <a href="http://www.usabride.com/newsletter">Daily
                        Newsletter</a>  or visit USABride's <a href="http://www.usabride.com/best%5fthing">Best
                              Thing Feature</a>.
                        </font>
